HEADWORD: Anecdotage
<hw>An"ec*do`tage</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Anecdotes
collectively; a collection of anecdotes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All history, therefore, being built partly, and some of it
altogether, upon <qex>anecdotage</qex>, must be a tissue of lies.</q>
<rj><qau>De Quincey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

